        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 4:24PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 423 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles north of Sunray, or 19 miles southeast of Stratford, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of west central
Hansford and southeastern Sherman Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
